Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light of summer is the radiance of yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.69,0:00:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the tears is a yellow sunflower.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unexpectedly, a sad case has occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.32,0:00:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how skillfully it's covered up,\Nthe sunflower will be the sole witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.93,0:00:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.56,0:02:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.76,0:02:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.69,0:02:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just heard... Inoue Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.90,0:02:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was an acquaintance of yours, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.70,0:02:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no words to express how sorry I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was about to ask her to make me the happiest man on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:28.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takaoka Akira (35)\NIndependent Film Director
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:28.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,For this to happen just when I was about to do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand how you must feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just who could've done this horrible deed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.09,0:02:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.89,0:02:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.85,0:02:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the coroner...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.68,0:02:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was between 11:00 AM and 1:00 PM today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflowers, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.66,0:03:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} loved these flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.46,0:03:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of person was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person that did such a thing to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what kind of a person were they!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ran a bar called "Sunflower."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gone there often.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.24,0:03:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflower?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thrusting its chest out to the sun that beats down on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.66,0:03:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon seeing its image, she would be able to\Ngather the strength and courage to carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, that's the legacy of the shop's namesake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.29,0:03:57.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And, when I went there yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:01.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She said happiness had finally come to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:02.80,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inoue Hiroko (38)\N"Sunflower" Bar Proprietor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She was already really overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did she mean, "happiness had finally come"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaokda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over there was Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's worked on directing independent films for the past seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.15,0:04:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A large movie studio asked him to direct a film for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.53,0:04:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear the movie was to be themed after the "crying-sands" of\NWhite Sands Beach, from his hometown in Fukushima Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he went there by himself last night to\Ndo a preliminary inspection of the filming site.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always believed in his talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.17,0:04:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing his day would come, she had\Nbeen financially supporting him all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.85,0:04:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just when those seven years of hard work had paid off...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really a heartbreaking blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.86,0:05:01.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old woman at the cigarette shop across the\Nstreet has been tending to her shop all day, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.74,0:05:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says she didn't see anyone go in or out of the\Napartment complex around the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only that afterwards, an electronics shop employee went\Ninto the complex with a large cardboard box, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.96,0:05:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was quite a while after, at approximately 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears it would have nothing to do with the current case, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Continue to gather information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.97,0:05:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person next to Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.22,0:05:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kitzuka Osamu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're both coworkers at a part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:38.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who discovered the body, and called 110.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who discovered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:47.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's hoping to become a scenario writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:51.08,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kitzuka Osamu (35)\NScenario Writer Hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:52.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Because Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had asked if he could borrow some story\Nideas from him, they arranged to meet in this room at 5:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.62,0:05:56.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The door was unlocked, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:05:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kitzuka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.71,0:06:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, has Takaoka come home yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After receiving the report, we arrived at 5:20.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.97,0:06:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little before that, Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrived home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.81,0:06:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd arrived about fifteen minutes later than the\Nappointed time due to being stuck in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:27.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was at his part-time job as a deliveryman for Oogata Electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 11:00 to 1:00, he was in the storeroom conducting inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.37,0:06:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you came to this apartment, the door wasn't locked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I wonder if Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} forgot to lock the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, usually, when women are home alone,\Nthey lock the door as a safety precaution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:07:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did often forget to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I had warned her more strongly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.23,0:07:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sort of thing wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A comedy program is the only one that's been circled in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it was so she wouldn't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.28,0:07:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did she like comedy programs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.25,0:07:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That might have been the case though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.38,0:07:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like she'd planned to watch\Nit today from 3:00 to 5:00 as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.38,0:07:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wasn't even able to watch her favorite television program...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.59,0:07:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A random crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.05,0:07:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, something's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.85,0:07:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.06,0:07:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that a photograph of?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.78,0:07:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked for Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi from 11:00\Nto 1:00, when Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:07:57.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was in Fukushima, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:07:57.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the filming site.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:08:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at White Sands Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.33,0:08:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he said he didn't see anyone else there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.67,0:08:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So his alibi cannot be substantiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He mentioned that he withdrew some money at a nearby bank...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And through the White Sands Police Station,\Nwe confirmed that with this photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was recorded on a security camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd always felt uneasy around them because\NI felt like I was being watched, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess this time I should be grateful for the security cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.15,0:08:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's not that we're suspecting you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened after you went back to the hotel last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you meet with anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.41,0:08:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no one at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At some point after midnight, I had room service come to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.46,0:08:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't I take this chance to detail\Nall of my movement from yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.05,0:09:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We usually use this in meetings with the cameramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as putting this down as a random crime, something's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.86,0:09:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, this is what was bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, the empty video case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 5:00 last night, I separated from Hiroko in front of the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.80,0:09:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was right when I had come to the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't loiter around touching that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.02,0:09:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This plug was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gave an interview at a newspaper company in\NFukushima a little past 10:00, if I remember correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:10:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the business cards of the\Ncameraman and the reporter I met with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.33,0:10:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These weren't removed in the normal way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the culprit kick them out of the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.05,0:10:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked out from the hotel the next\Nmorning, at a little past 8:00 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.01,0:10:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The voucher and the receipt, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 2:27 in the morning, and the order was curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s signature is also present.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, his alibi for the night is also proven without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it, so that's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the bank's security camera caught me at a little past 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, from last night to a little past noon today,\Nyou didn't set one foot outside of Fukushima, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:10:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:11:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A beautiful alibi with no flaws or time left unaccounted for!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't do that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just go around touching things!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:08.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot that Uncle Kogoro asked for some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.81,0:11:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted these investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.90,0:11:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Investigated?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag and her shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.74,0:11:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said they were important in determining who the\Nculprit is, so it was an extremely urgent request.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, here are the things you requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, earlier, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.22,0:11:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prepare an investigation headquarters for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to take a look at the modus operandi\Nof each known burglar and look for witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've probably had the strength drained from you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:12:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, in memory of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as well as for your own sake,\Npull yourself together quickly and create a great work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.95,0:12:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.29,0:12:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, through Detective Takagi's efforts,\Na number of true facts have been confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True facts?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.71,0:12:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.04,0:12:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please take a look inside the video appliance for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.14,0:12:31.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a tape inside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.77,0:12:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what had been recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.48,0:12:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please rewind it a bit and play it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.52,0:12:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:40.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't this a rerun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.49,0:12:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched this program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about a month ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.45,0:12:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The overturned chair leg caught on the\Ncord, and unplugged it from the outlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably during the struggle with the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.29,0:13:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the fact that it had been recorded up until there...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.92,0:13:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit didn't know that Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been recording it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had been cut off about 3/4ths of the way into the 2-hour special.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.10,0:13:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started recording at 3:00, and was cut off an hour and a half later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the room was thrown into disarray at approximately 4:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is not the same time at which the murder took place, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking the culprit murdered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} during the day, and then\Nreturned here again in the evening to rummage around for something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a bit hard to imagine that being the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit murdered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} between 11:00 and 1:00 at\Na separate location, and after transporting her body here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.71,0:13:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Threw the room into disarray in order to make\Nit appear as if it was all the result of a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.26,0:13:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, if you could give the thing you found to the Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.81,0:13:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:13:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like ordinary sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was found at the rear of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoe, underneath the insole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.99,0:14:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the crime scene investigator research it and\Nhe said it was something called "crying sand".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.29,0:14:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crying sand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.42,0:14:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a high composition of quartz, a rare type\Nof sand that only exists at unpolluted beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are twenty such beaches in the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them is White Sands Beach in Fukushima Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.80,0:14:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, it is the beach at which\NTakaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was location hunting yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.85,0:14:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, perhaps you telephoned Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely saying something akin to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.02,0:14:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I've finished location hunting, so how about you come over\Nhere to Fukushima so we can spend some time together?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Accordingly, Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} set up her recorder to record\Nthe comedy program she had wanted to watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.74,0:14:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And headed to Fukushima early this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meeting time was after 12:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after you showed yourself to the bank's security camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got to the beach first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.55,0:15:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was the beach which was to become\Nthe stage for the film her lover was to direct...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably had some special feelings for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.10,0:15:23.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.07,0:15:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The White Sands Beach is in your hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were very familiar with the times\Nat which no one would be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you quickly took off in your car and came\Nback to the area around this apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.67,0:15:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You parked in a place where there were unlikely to be any witnesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, after dressing as a deliveryman, delivered the cardboard\Nappliance box containing the body to this apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so the electronics shop employee that was witnessed at 4:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you disguised using the uniform and hat\Nfrom the company you work part-time for, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please stop that kind of talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that just because I was silently listening\Nto your story that I'd be taken to be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.21,0:16:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you—?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.92,0:16:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears he just remembered something\Nelse I had asked him to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.76,0:16:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, allow me to continue my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having transported Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make the scene look as if she had been murdered during\Nthe struggle with the burglar, you threw the room into disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.69,0:16:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you disposed of the cardboard box,\Nthe hat, and the uniform somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:17:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, saying that you had been caught in traffic, you purposely\Nshowed up later than the meeting time with Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.20,0:17:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing so, you made it seem as if\NHiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.05,0:17:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you could fabricate your alibi of having\Nbeen in Fukushima at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your deduction is that I called\NHiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to White Sands Beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then that I murdered her there between 11:00 and 1:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to be under the impression that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there really isn't any evidence that Hiroko went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.61,0:17:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please look inside the envelope\Nthat Detective Takagi brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an article from this morning's issue\Nof the Fukushima daily newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably from the interview he gave yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.96,0:17:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That newspaper clipping was inside the pocket of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:18:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After she arrived in Fukushima, Hiroko san had bought a newspaper\Nsince she knew that you had given an interview yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just a brief mention, but since it was about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was the top news of the day,\Nmore important than any of the other articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a reward for her unwavering support these many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flower bud had fully opened; the large sunflower had blossomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably treasured it with dancing emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko never came!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.46,0:18:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought the Fukushima newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.75,0:18:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I cut it out and put it in her bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.13,0:18:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you ever looked closely at the words\Nwritten on that picture on the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Gazing only at you"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the language of flowers, that is what sunflowers represent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.68,0:18:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that was Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.06,0:18:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about if you admit your crime, and atone for what you've done?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.28,0:18:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did not murder Hiroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.33,0:19:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.58,0:19:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.95,0:19:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.88,0:19:14.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sending you the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks to be sand, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.97,0:19:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There shouldn't be anything like that there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.89,0:19:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made sure that the blanket—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.01,0:19:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Made sure that the blanket" what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you going to say after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.56,0:19:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Was rid of all the sand," perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a trace amount, but there is still some under the blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, that sand is probably the\Nsame as the aforementioned crying sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please explain why there is some remaining in the trunk of your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.04,0:19:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you really want to break up with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.96,0:19:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it because your luck has turned?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.75,0:19:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say it's that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know just how much I've\Nsuffered through purely for your sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.97,0:20:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now you're going to treat me as a burden?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have you return the favor to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.31,0:20:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a spare key in Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed it for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Hiroko had intended to have me support her from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.99,0:20:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me to be bound to her my entire life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew I had to protect my independence somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.66,0:20:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your guesswork was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.87,0:20:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw through my trick by sheer chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, take a look at the\Npotted sunflower on the floor there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.88,0:20:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you feel anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know how it was in Fukushima, but in this town\Nthere were no clouds—it was a beautiful Japanese day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so what of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.73,0:20:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room faces south.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.44,0:21:01.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Additionally, the curtains were pulled back, so\Nthere was absolutely nothing to block the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.24,0:21:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that potted plant had fallen between\N11:00 and 1:00, the time of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the time from then until 5:00, when Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} discovered the\Nbody, the sunflowers would have been exposed to plenty of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunlight is energy for sunflowers to bloom\Nin, so naturally the flowers would...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flowers were face down, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, I surmised that the potted flowers were toppled\Nmuch later, perhaps right before the body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.93,0:21:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, I revised my reasoning accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, you figured it out well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.19,0:21:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there is one flaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.45,0:21:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was after everything was over, and I was leaving...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That those sunflowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.66,0:22:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was probably due to some sort of chance\Nthat the dirt inside had become unbalanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.34,0:22:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never laid one finger on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it seems he said that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.31,0:23:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you fell in order to make the truth known.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.81,0:23:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the flower that had fallen from Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:23:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does Uncle have a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking it's like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.36,0:23:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.32,0:23:57.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sunflower is his captive audience...
